==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Using many [[conjunctions]] to achieve an overwhelming effect in a sentence. 

The opposite of [[asyndeton]]. Both polysyndeton and asyndeton are examples of rhetorical schemes.

====Examples====
* I still need to sweep the floor and wash the windows and take out the trash and empty the dishwasher.
* This semester, I'm taking math and physics and history and astronomy and band.